wrapper classes : java.lang
used to represent primitive as an object

------------
Byte
Short           Numeric wrapper classes
Integer
Long
Float
Double
--------------
Character
Boolean

Constructors :
primitive to wrapper object conversion : Boxing
1 primitive : Byte (byte) ,Short(short)
             Integer obj = new Integer(10);
             Double obj1 = new Double (35.5);
             
2. String  : except Character : Integer (String),Long(String)
             Byte obj = new Byte ("10");
             Float obj1 = new Float("20.7");
             Byte obj2 = Byte("10.8");//NumberFormatException
             Integer obj3 = new Integer("abc");//NumberFormatException
             
Methods : 
1. xxxValue(): byteValue(),shortValue(),intValue(),longValue(),floatValue(),doubleValue(),
 To convert wrapper object into primitive : Unboxing
 
 2.Static WrapperObject valueOf(primitive) : Primitive to wrapper conversion : Boxing
 
      Integer : public static Integer valueOf(int)
      Double  : public static Double valueOf(double)
      Byte    : public static Byte valueOf(byte)
      
    e.g short s = 20;
        short obj = Short.valueOf(s);
        
3.static wrapperObject valueOf(String) : 

      Integer : public static Integer valueOf(String)
      Double  : public static Double valueOf(String)
      Byte    : public static Byte valueOf(String)
      
    e.g  Short obj = Short.valueOf("20");
    
    
    
    
    java 5 feature :
    Auro Boxing and auto Unboxing
    //before java 5 
    Integer obj = new Integer(10);//Boixing
    //After java 5
    Integer obj =10;//Auto Boxing  
    
    
    Collection : is a framework
    
    
    